-- TD Hires Morgan Stanley’s Perry to Run European Currency
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-04-23T16:23:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-23/td-hires-morgan-stanley-s-perry-to-run-european-currency-trading.html
Toronto-Dominion Bank (TD) , Canada’s
second-largest lender, hired  Morgan Stanley (MS) ’s Brian Perry as
head of European currency trading for its securities unit.  Perry, who ran the U.K., European and Middle Eastern Real
Money Sales business for Morgan Stanley, will join TD Securities
in London on July 15 as a managing director, the Toronto-based
firm said today in an e-mailed statement. He will report to
Michael Gibbens, TD Securities’s global head of foreign
exchange.  Before joining Morgan Stanley, Perry worked for  Royal Bank
of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) , according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
